				\begin{document}$$\:{\gamma\:}_{a}=\frac{{f}_{s}-{f}_{a}}{{f}_{s}}\times\:100\%$$\end{document}

It can be seen from the above analysis that when the H/W is 2, the middle of the CPB is in a state of uniaxial compression, and the end effect is small. At this time, the UCS is closest to the actual UCS of the CPB. Therefore, taking the UCS of the CPB with an H/W of 2 as the reference value, in order to make the regression model fit the various parameters of the UCS calculation, the non-linear fitting method was used to establish the UCS conversion model of the CPB with an H/W of 2 and an H/W of 0.5 and 1, respectively. This conversion model adopts the power function product model, such as formula (3):3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
